      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** ** The diagonal or \"constant diagram\" functor \u0394 *)\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Section diagonal_functor.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Context `{Funext}.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Variables C D : PreCategory.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n  (**\n     Quoting Dwyer and Spalinski:\n\n     There is a diagonal or ``constant diagram'' functor\n\n<<\n     \u0394 : C \u2192 C\u1d30,\n>>\n\n     which carries an object [X : C] to the constant functor [\u0394 X : D\n     -> C] (by definition, this ``constant functor'' sends each object\n     of [D] to [X] and each morphism of [D] to [Identity X]). The\n     functor \u0394 assigns to each morphism [f : X -> X'] of [C] the\n     constant natural transformation [t(f) : \u0394 X -> \u0394 X'] determined\n     by the formula [t(f) d = f] for each object [d] of [D].  **)\n\n  (** We use [C\u00b9] rather than [C] for judgemental compatibility with\n      Kan extensions. *)\n\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Definition diagonal_functor : Functor (1 -> C) (D -> C)\n    := @pullback_along _ D 1 C (Functors.to_terminal _).",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Definition diagonal_functor' : Functor C (D -> C)\n    := diagonal_functor o ExponentialLaws.Law1.Functors.inverse _.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n  "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Section convert.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n    "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Lemma diagonal_functor_diagonal_functor' X\n    : diagonal_functor X = diagonal_functor' (X (center _)).",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": [
        {
          "_type": "goal",
          "name": null,
          "conclusion": "(diagonal_functor _0 X)%object =\n(diagonal_functor' _0 (X _0 (center 1)))%object",
          "hypotheses": [
            {
              "_type": "hypothesis",
              "names": [
                "H"
              ],
              "body": null,
              "type": "Funext"
            },
            {
              "_type": "hypothesis",
              "names": [
                "C"
              ],
              "body": null,
              "type": "PreCategory"
            },
            {
              "_type": "hypothesis",
              "names": [
                "D"
              ],
              "body": null,
              "type": "PreCategory"
            },
            {
              "_type": "hypothesis",
              "names": [
                "X"
              ],
              "body": null,
              "type": "(1 -> C)%category"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n    "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Proof.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": [
        {
          "_type": "goal",
          "name": null,
          "conclusion": "(diagonal_functor _0 X)%object =\n(diagonal_functor' _0 (X _0 (center 1)))%object",
          "hypotheses": [
            {
              "_type": "hypothesis",
              "names": [
                "H"
              ],
              "body": null,
              "type": "Funext"
            },
            {
              "_type": "hypothesis",
              "names": [
                "C"
              ],
              "body": null,
              "type": "PreCategory"
            },
            {
              "_type": "hypothesis",
              "names": [
                "D"
              ],
              "body": null,
              "type": "PreCategory"
            },
            {
              "_type": "hypothesis",
              "names": [
                "X"
              ],
              "body": null,
              "type": "(1 -> C)%category"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n      "
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "path_functor.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": [
